The paper deals with visual commonsense reasoning, which involves understanding visual scenes and answering questions based on them. This falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a new model architecture and discusses its performance, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves text-to-image grounding, which is a topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
